From e25d2bc06a884d0ebdb41b5cc189bf62ff0460da Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Girish Kumar M P <gmp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 30 May 2025 17:10:03 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] wifi: ath12k: Handle dp tid setup and cleanup for UMAC
 Migration

UMAC Migration involves transferring the Primary TQM from one firmware
to another without disconnecting the MLD peer.

Add Api's to send HAL_REO_CMD_FLUSH_QUEUE and HAL_REO_CMD_UNBLOCK_CACHE
reo commands.

Currently performing tid setup for the new primary peer incase of
dp_setup_done bit is not set for the peer.

Tid cleanup is performed for the old primary peer only after the
migration is success.

Patch Dependency: ALL UMAC migration patches [994 Series]
FR 105112: Ath12k Core Infrastructure for UMAC Migration

Signed-off-by: Girish Kumar M P <gmp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Co-Developed by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
